fields.title: Commander Keen
fields.description: Commander Keen is a classic series of platformer video games developed by id Software and published by Apogee Software. First released in 1990, the series was one of the earliest and most influential shareware games on PC. It follows the adventures of Billy Blaze, an eight-year-old genius who dons the persona of "Commander Keen" to defend Earth and the galaxy from alien threats. Armed with his homemade spaceship and a neural stunner, Keen embarks on adventures across different worlds and encounters a variety of quirky alien races and challenges.

fields.title: Mega Man Zero/ZX Legacy Collection
fields.description: Mega Man Zero/ZX Legacy Collection is a compilation of six action-packed games from Capcom's Mega Man franchise, combining the Mega Man Zero series (originally for Game Boy Advance) and the Mega Man ZX series (from Nintendo DS). Released in 2020 for modern platforms, this collection includes enhanced versions of these beloved 2D side-scrollers, offering a fresh experience for new players while also appealing to longtime fans of the series.

fields.title: Time Commando
fields.description: Time Commando is an action-adventure video game developed by Adeline Software International and published by Electronic Arts and Activision. Released in 1996 for PlayStation and PC, with later versions for the Sega Saturn, Time Commando was notable for its innovative concept and unique blend of combat across different historical time periods. The game is a third-person, single-player experience, offering an immersive, time-traveling narrative.

fields.title: A Flappy Bird in Real Life
fields.description: is a simulation game inspired by the original Flappy Bird, where the player controls a bird that must navigate through a series of pipes without hitting them. The game emphasizes realistic physics, sounds, and visuals, enhancing the classic experience with a more immersive and authentic feel. The objective remains the same: guide the bird as far as possible without crashing. Released on October 31, 2018, it's a simple yet challenging game that focuses on precision and timing.

fields.title: Mega Man X Legacy Collection
fields.description: Mega Man X Legacy Collection is a compilation of the iconic Mega Man X series, developed and published by Capcom. Released in 2018 for various platforms, including PlayStation 4, Xbox One, Nintendo Switch, and PC, this collection brings together the first eight games in the Mega Man X franchise, which originally debuted on the Super Nintendo Entertainment System (SNES) in 1993. The collection is split into two volumes: Volume 1 includes the first four games, while Volume 2 features the remaining titles.

fields.title: Heroesx of Might & Magicx III - HD Edition
fields.description: Heroesx of Might & Magicx III - HD Edition is a remastered version of the classic turn-based strategy game Heroes of Might and Magic III, originally released in 1999. Developed by DotEmu and published by Ubisoft, this HD Edition was launched in January 2015, revitalizing the beloved title for modern audiences while preserving the core gameplay that made it a fan favorite.

fields.title: Counter-Strike
fields.description: Counter-Strike is a tactical first-person shooter developed by Valve Corporation and released in 2000. It is one of the most popular and influential titles in the Counter-Strike series, which began as a mod for Half-Life. Known for its competitive gameplay and emphasis on teamwork and strategy, Counter-Strike 1.6 has maintained a dedicated player base for over two decades.

fields.title: Dark Souls 3
fields.description: Dark Souls 3 is an action role-playing game (RPG) developed by FromSoftware and published by Bandai Namco Entertainment. Released in 2016, it is the fourth entry in the Souls series and follows the highly acclaimed Dark Souls and Dark Souls II. The game is set in a dark, decaying world where the player takes on the role of the Ashen One, an undead warrior tasked with linking the fire and preventing the end of the world.
